      "rationale": "H-refinement convergence study across four mesh densities demonstrated stiffness QoI convergence within 1.4% and GCI of 3.1% on peak von Mises stress. Richardson-extrapolated discretization error meets the pre-specified 2% threshold. Medium mesh (52 k elements) selected for production runs balancing accuracy and runtime."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Newton-Raphson residual force norm < 0.1% of reaction force at each converged increment.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analyses used sparse direct solver (SPARSE) with tight convergence tolerance (force criterion 0.001). Residual norms monitored across all load steps; maximum observed residual 0.06% of reaction force. Solver error contribution to QoI uncertainty negligible relative to material and geometric uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts by a second qualified engineer.",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed independently by a second FEA engineer not involved in original model construction. Boundary condition application, contact definitions, and post-processing scripts verified against ASTM F1717 test protocol. One minor discrepancy (load application offset) corrected prior to production runs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic model with isotropic hardening justified for Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw under quasi-static monotonic loading; geometric nonlinearity enabled.",
      "rationale": "Elastic-plastic J2 plasticity with isotropic hardening (Ramberg-Osgood fit to tensile coupon data) is appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V under quasi-static monotonic compression-bending. Geometric nonlinearity (NLGEOM ON) captures large-displacement effects observed experimentally at 40 mm displacement. Fracture not modeled; model scope limited to pre-fracture regime consistent with COU QoIs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile coupon testing; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of production screws; uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo propagation.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and hardening parameters derived from six tensile coupons machined from the same Ti-6Al-4V bar stock as the tested constructs. Screw geometry inputs from CMM measurements (n=5 screws). Monte Carlo propagation (n=1000 samples) quantified combined material and geometric input uncertainty; 95th-percentile bounds included in E/uval calculation."
    },
