      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to the clinical risk of screw or rod fatigue failure. Regulatory precedent (FDA guidance on spinal implant testing) confirms these QoIs are appropriate surrogates for in vivo mechanical performance."
